The paper deals with the problem of minimizing Age of Information (AoI) in wireless networks, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also considers interference constraints and time-varying channels, which are topics related to control systems (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.MA). Additionally, the paper proposes two scheduling policies, which involve optimization and decision-making, respectively, and thus could be related to machine learning (cs.LG).
